{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778247784,"nonce":"O5Ddo7SA+SHyWVRNKqs8E/VVNEU=","message":"**Empirical peak-velocity Δv on trained flavor-B controllers — negative-sign headline.**\n\nCompanion to the analytical Δv predictions (§5.3 / §7.2 of synthesis doc). Single canonical reach (15 cm forward, init=(0,0), target=(0.15,0)), SISU=0.5, no test-time perturbation, eval_seed=42, 5 internal replicates × 3 seeds × 3 η_max = 45 trained replicates. Baseline: `baseline_standard_12k` GRU, mean peak forward velocity 1.643 m/s.\n\nΔv % = (pv_target − pv_baseline) / pv_baseline × 100 (matches `compute_velocity_inflation`, `f90bf74`).\n\n| η_max | mean peak forward velocity (m/s) | mean Δv % | SD Δv % |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 0.03 | 1.302 | **−20.75** | 40.80 |\n| 0.10 | 1.209 | **−26.40** | 36.55 |\n| 0.30 | 1.221 | **−25.68** | 40.88 |\n\n**Headline.** Trained flavor-B controllers are *slower* than baseline at every η_max. η_max stratification is weak (~6% between conditions vs ~40% within-condition SD).\n\n**Bimodality.** Replicate-level Δv distribution is bimodal: ~20–27% of replicates land at +40 to +57%, the rest at −12 to −73%. The negative *mean* reflects a majority-negative replicate population, not a small uniform shift.\n\n**Contrast with corrected analytical Δv.** The full-state-$B_w$ fix on `feature/cs-faithful-riccati-investigation` (SHA `0c160e9`) makes the analytical Δv on the rlrmp regime **positive** (§4.2-revised, §5.4-revised). Empirical and analytical disagree in *sign* at the group mean. The (a)/(b) framing is moot here — the joint conclusion is that flavor-B training is not converging to the analytical H∞ optimum.\n\nArtifacts: `results/part2_5/peak_velocity_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md` (commit `4657029`); `_artifacts/part2_5/runs/peak_velocity_flavor_b/summary.json`. Cross-cutting note on `4d38c15` follows.","files":null}]}